description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/2284/documentation

The dataset represents the production of 1 kg of fluorescent whitening agent triazinylaminostilben type from 4-nitrotoluene, phenol, and ethylene oxide.;Material and energy inputs as well as production of waste and emissions are from literature resources. Infrastructure and transport are estimation based on a large chemical plant.;Flow diagram of the production of the fluorescent white agent DAS-1 (triazinylaminostilbene type): ;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]

From reception of precursors calcite, stylvite, and sodium chlorid at the factory gate.

This activity ends with the production of 1 kg of fluroescent whitening agent triazinylaminostilben type. The dataset includes material and energy input, production of waste, emissions to air and water, transport and infrastructure.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: data from European main producer, used as European average
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The starting material for the triazinylaminostilbenes is 4,4‘-Dinitrostilbene-2,2‘-disulphonic acid, which is produced by oxidation of 4-nitrotoluene-2-sulphonic acid with sodium hypochlorite. A subsequent Béchamps reduction with iron fillings and HCl gives 4,4‘-diaminostilbene-2,2‘-disulphonic acid, that is reacted at both amino groups with cyanuric chloride. The two remaining Cl atoms in the cyanuric chloride rings then react one after another with two amines, in the case of DAS-1 with aniline and morpholine. Subsequent steps produce the desired -crystal modification and deliver the finished commercial product, that contains 67% active substance.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: aggregated data, calculated by the producing company itself

exchanges.description:
Fluorescent whitening agents (FWA) are colorless organic substances that are able to absorb ultraviolet radiance and to re-emit the absorbed energy as blue fluorescent light (400 - 500 nm). FWAs are used as additives in detergents. By coating the textile fibres during the washing process, they compensate the natural (but continuosly increasing) yellow touch of the textiles resulting in a high grade of whiteness.
